title: Pirates run for 448, stop Space Coast
text:
Pirates run for 448, stop Space Coast CARL KOTALA, FOR FLORIDA TODAY 11:21 p.m. EDT October 15, 2015 Palm Bay High’s Chase Harris gains yardage up the middle against Space Coast Jr./Sr. High on Thursday night. (Photo: Craig Rubadoux/FLORIDA TODAY) 
MELBOURNE — When you have an offensive line that has been blocking as well as Palm Bay’s front five has this season, it’s pretty easy to understand why Pirate running backs look forward to each and every carry.
